In Bridge World Standard, the 3@C rebid distinguishes a really bad hand from one with a little something. The double-negative rebid allows the bidding to stop at three of opener's original major suit. Responder shows values by bidding anything else. With a natural club bid, the best he can do is stall with two notrump. With support for opener's major, he can raise directly (a double raise shows strong trumps, and little else) or jump in a short suit, a splinter raise.|
